A similar resistance pattern could occur with pandemic (H1N1) 2009 virus. Regardless of the mutational mechanism for antiviral drug resistance, mass use of antiviral drugs could potentially lead to selection pressure for drug-resistant viruses (
 
  7
 ). Experience with seasonal influenza demonstrated the fitness of some oseltamivir-resistant strains (
 
  8
